THIS COMPLEX SOLUTION WAS MIXED WITH AN EQUAL VOLUME OF PRECIPITANT CONTAINING 24-33% PEG 4000, 0.2 M LI2SO4, 0.1 M TRIS CL (PH 7.9-8.4), 5% GLYCEROL, AND EQUILIBRATED WITH THE PRECIPITANT BY HANGING DROP VAPOR DIFFUSION AT 277 K. NOTE THAT THE INHIBITOR IS ACTUALLY A RACEMIC MIXTURE OF 39B AND ITS ENANTIOMER, HERE CALLED 39E. IT IS THE RACEMATE THAT IS BOUND IN THE CRYSTAL, REPRESENTED IN THE COORDINATES AS A 1:1 STATISTICALLY-DISORDERED MIXTURE OF 39B AND 39E.
